When I was little, I dreamed of the ocean.
A wild place, very colorful and full of life, housing strange and fantastic creatures.
I imagined big sharks reigning supreme and graceful sea turtles swirling through the corals.
First a marine biologist, then a photographer, I spent most of my career seeking places as magical as those I dreamed of as a child.
As you can see, I started exploring the water very early on.
But the first time I really went underwater, I was about 10 years old.
I clearly remember kicking my fins determinedly to reach that old cannon embedded in a shallow coral reef.
When I finally managed to catch it, I looked up and found myself surrounded by fish of every color of the rainbow.
That day, I fell in love with the ocean.
